Love George O'Brien and his brand of B western. The RKO movies on this DVD were a good, clear transfer and enjoyable to watch It's just too bad there weren't more of these made during the pre-WWII era.
Great collection! Enjoyed all 9 films. Picture and sound quality on this WB Archive dvd were great.

George O'Brien was just about the ONLY cowboy on the silver screen who rarely got himself in a seemingly hopeless situation. That is what I think made him better than J.W., R.R., L.R., G.A.and all the others.
This series was fun to watch.  There was plenty of action with the hero winning in the end.  Good one for the "B" grade fan.
It was excellent, I really enjoyed them old westerns, good entertainment, no profanity or nudity.
